cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.IR 

This paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) and deep learning models for Arabic text diacritization. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses enhancements such as embeddings and Conditional Random Field (CRF), which are common in machine learning (ML) and deep learning (DL) research, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. Additionally, the paper proposes a novel approach for machine translation (MT) using diacritics, which falls under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of Block-Normalized Gradient (BNG) also suggests the possibility of the paper belonging to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper discusses the evaluation of the models, which could fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
